en_524478_0	A group of more than 20 Army personnel of the 11 Division and the Signal Training School at Buwelikada of the Security Force Headquarters - Central (SFHQ-Cen) voluntarily donated their blood to support a project, launched by the Welfare Association of the District Court in Kandy.
en_524478_1	The blood is to be used for patients receiving treatment at Kandy Teaching Hospital.
en_524478_2	Welfare Association of District Court Kandy in a letter to the 11 Division Headquarters sought the assistance of the Army for donation of blood since the organization has a high regard for members of the armed forces.
en_524478_3	The donation campaign took place on Thursday (15) at the Kandy District Court premises.
